ce:section.ce:para:
The weight-average molecular weights (M

                           w
                        ) of samples (after acetylation [22]) were estimated using a LC20 gel permeation chromatography (GPC) system (Shimadzu Corp., Japan) equipped with a TSKgel GMPWXL column (300 mm × 7.8 mm) and a refractometric detector. The eluent was an isocratic 100% tetrahydrofuran (THF, HPLC grade without stabilizer) at a flow rate of 1.0 mL·min−1 and the column temperature was kept at 35 °C. Each sample (~0.5%) in THF was injected after passing through a 0.45 μm filter and detected by a variable wavelength detector, while the apparent molecular weight was calibrated using polystyrene standards.
